      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm looking at some of the logs from the latest moderation sweep. Can you help me optimize this regex pattern? It's currently catching too many false positives in the comments section and slowing down the processing queue. \n\n`regex: /s[a-z]+[0-9]{3}/g`\n\nIt's supposed to flag specific alphanumeric sequences, but it's hitting way too many normal words. How can I tighten this up so it only hits the exact pattern we discussed in the spec?",
